A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Christy Todd, Georgia's 2024 Teacher of the Year; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, a proper quality education for the young people of this state is the single most
3 important objective of the General Assembly; and
4 WHEREAS, in recognition of her outstanding dedication to the teaching profession, Christy
5 Todd was named the Georgia Teacher of the Year in January 2024 as well as one of four
6 finalists for the National Teacher of the Year; and
7 WHEREAS, during her tenure as Georgia Teacher of the Year, she delivered more than 125
8 keynote presentations statewide that focused on the importance of strengthening connections
9 to support public education and presented recommendations on ways to make Georgia the
10 top state for teachers; and
11 WHEREAS, she has been instrumental in fostering the next generation of educators by
12 partnering with high schools, universities, and teacher associations, reaching more than 1,000
13 prospective educators to highlight the impact and influence of the teaching profession; and
