14 WHEREAS, during her distinguished teaching career, she spent 15 years at Rising Starr
15 Middle School in Fayette County Public Schools, where she served as chorus director and
16 later founded the district's Community for Creativity initiative; and
17 WHEREAS, she now serves in a leadership role at the Georgia Department of Education,
18 overseeing cross-departmental projects aimed at supporting teacher recruitment and retention
19 while expanding the teacher pipeline; and
20 WHEREAS, in addition to her classroom and leadership contributions, she has an extensive
21 background in nonprofit consulting and business development, is a published researcher, and
22 is a founding member of the Story Arts Collective, an organization committed to growing
23 Georgia's creative workforce; and
24 WHEREAS, in recognition of such remarkable contributions to the education and welfare
25 of Georgia's students, it is abundantly fitting and proper for this body to honor the
26 extraordinary accomplishments and academic achievements of this outstanding educator.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body commend Christy Todd, Georgia's 2024 Teacher of the Year, for
29 her extraordinary contributions to education and express their most sincere best wishes for
30 continued success.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
33 Christy Todd.
